RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOEY THE FISH got bumped at the start by UKRAINIAN PRINCESS, who recovered outwards from a bobble, grew detached at the tail of the field when devoid of speed early on chasing three to four paths off the inside, tucked inside through the turn coming under coaxing near the three-eighths, spun three wide for home making headway, rallied with choppy action in behind in her hind legs and was up in the last jumps to prevail. UKRAINIAN PRINCESS bobbled at the start recovering outwards and bumping the aforementioned foe, chased four to five wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled four wide for home, rallied to take command three-sixteenths out, dug in under a drive and was caught in the final strides to the finish. MAIZE LOVED LAFFY showed the way in hand along the inside under some pressure from a pair early on before shaking those foes off placed to coaxing near the three-eighths, got confronted by MY GORGEOUS and was headed for command at the five-sixteenths, took the inside route into upper stretch taking back narrow command, got headed at the three-sixteenths for good and weakened to the finish. MY GORGEOUS chased along the inside and then just off the inside into the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths and advancing to take command at the five-sixteenths, spun two to three wide for home relinquishing the front and weakened in the stretch. REIGN OF THUNDER chased three to four wide in aim of the front early on, came under coaxing at the three-eighths and faded, swung four to five wide into upper stretch and folded. FRANKIE KNOWS BEST chased two to three wide prompting the pace early on before settling in range of the leader, came under coaxing from the three-eighths and began to retreat, swung three to four wide into upper stretch and faltered.

ROYAL MEGHAN leaned out at the start, settled at the rear on the outside, was roused four wide on the turn, moved out into upper stretch and lacked the needed response then just missed the show. BLUE PAYNT was well placed towards the front, dropped back late on the backstretch, moved from the inside to the two path around the turn and came up empty. TRIPLE P settled near the back, was urged two then three wide around the turn and failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VAX dueled inside of SWEET LIBERTY from the get go coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, took the inside route into upper stretch, continued to battle head to head through the stretch to the finish drifting out late and gamely held on to prevail. SWEET LIBERTY dueled from the two path with VAX to her inside, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and spun just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in under a drive fighting gamely in head to head combat through to the wire but was ultimately denied at the end. GOOD ACCELEBRATE broke out at the start and was corrected, chased four then three wide down the backstretch before tucking to the inside seven-sixteenths from home, came under coaxing three furlongs out, continued in the inside route into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick. GRACEFULNESS broke out at the start and was corrected, chased just off the inside under coaxing from the three-eighths, spun two to three wide for home and improved position for the last major share. CUT THE CHECK three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, tipped three to four wide into upper stretch and tired. SNOWY EVENING away to an awkward beginning, chased along the inside under a ride from the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and tired. BANDULU QUEEN chased four paths off the inside down the backstretch before tucking three then two wide through the turn under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, angled three to four wide at the head of the stretch and trailed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PATRICK THE GREAT went to the front then shook clear early, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked in the two path around the turn, responded well under a strong hand-ride in upper stretch, was put to a right-handed crop outside the furlong marker, disposed of the runner-up inside that marker, drew off under a drive to near the sixteenth-pole then was placed under a hand-ride while much the best. MIDNIGHT EXPRESS followed the solo leader down the backstretch, was urged along passing the nine-sixteenths, gained late on the backstretch, chased in the three path around the turn, made a bid outside the quarter-pole, fought outside of the winner to the furlong marker then proved no match while clear for the place. REUNION TOUR acted-up just before the start and was last to commence but broke with the rest of the field, was urged along off the pace, moved closer near the nine-sixteenths, chased in the four path around the turn and tired while able to get the show. BERNARDINO was hustled from the gate then urged along off the pace, rounded the turn in the two path, angled out while still on his inside lead in upper stretch then swapped to the proper lead and failed to threaten. BOINTHEBACK dropped back near the three-quarter pole, went two then three wide around the turn, swung six wide into the stretch and was no factor. TYRANNOSAURUS REX settled on the outside, was roused late on the backstretch, went four wide under urging on the turn and failed to respond. TIZA BROWN settled on the inside, saved ground under urging on the turn, turned into the stretch in the two path under the crop and faltered. TIMES WERE ADDED AFTER VIDEO REVIEW.
